From eadea71f0728c284551ed2d6ec1d3c67aa9e5626 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mike <leemichael289@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 20 Feb 2026 19:27:45 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 2/7] feat: add hyperclaw-security plugin and browser URL
 approval gate
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Core patch (browser-tool.ts):
- Pre-navigate approval gate using exec.approval.request infrastructure
- Checks ~/.openclaw/browser-approvals.json allowlist before navigating
- Blocks navigation and requests human approval (via Telegram/Discord) for unknown hosts
- allow-always decision automatically adds hostname to browser-approvals.json
- Fails securely: unknown URLs blocked if approval system unavailable

New infra (src/infra/browser-approvals.ts):
- URL allowlist management mirroring exec-approvals.ts pattern
- Supports hostname, wildcard (*.example.com), and URL prefix patterns
- AES-256-GCM compatible file format for future encryption

New plugin (extensions/hyperclaw-security/):
- history-logger: JSONL session logs via llm_input/output + tool call hooks
  Output: ~/.openclaw/logs/history/YYYY/MM/DD/<sessionId>.jsonl
- attack-logger: incident stream + Telegram alerts for security events
  Output: ~/.openclaw/logs/attacks/YYYY/MM/DD/<incidentId>.json
- report_injection tool: panasonic chat_api report_user pattern — model
  self-reports detected prompt injections for SFT training data collection
- secrets-store: AES-256-GCM encrypted local vault, key derived from
  OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_TOKEN via PBKDF2
- deposit_secret tool: injects vault secrets into browser form fields;
  secret value never returned to model; Telegram approval for unapproved hosts
- secrets-redact hook: tool_result_persist belt-and-suspenders redaction

